OL,7,FAfterwards, Hazel Huggins' family paid
OL,8,Ftribute to her, describing her as a
OL,9,Fwoman with a 'radiant spirit' and as a
OL,10,F'bright shining light, loved by many.'
OL,12,FThe court heard that Huggins suffered
OL,13,Fwith Borderline Personality Disorder,
OL,14,Fanxiety and depression. He moved out
OL,15,Fof the family home two months before
OL,16,Fthe killing due to their concerns
OL,17,Fabout his behaviour.
