OL,7,FMr Huggins had also started to receive
OL,8,FWhatsApp messages from his son, saying
OL,9,Fhe was sorry and to call the police.
OL,11,FWhile on the 999 call he received
OL,12,Ffurther messages where his son talked
OL,13,Fof his mother 'passing peacefully' and
OL,14,Fabout him being armed with knives in
OL,15,F'self-defence.'
OL,17,FAt the same time police had phoned
OL,18,FBradley Huggins following his unclear
OL,19,F999 call. It was then that he
OL,20,Fconfessed to the killing.
