OL,7,FIn the police interview, Huggins made
OL,8,Fa full and frank admission to his
OL,9,Factions, saying there had been
OL,10,Ffriction between him and his mother
OL,11,F'over a mixture of things.'
OL,13,FThe attack was triggered when Mrs
OL,14,FHuggins told him he wasn't going to
OL,15,Freceive some money he felt was due to
OL,16,Fhim.
OL,18,FHe became angry and turned on her,
OL,19,Fpicking up the knife and attacking her
OL,20,Fin the doorway of the kitchen and then
OL,21,Fthe bedroom.
